And you shall count from the day after the Sabbath, from the
day that you brought the sheaf of the wave offering; seven full
weeks shall they be; continuing fifty days to the day after the
seventh Sabbath; then you shall present a cereal offering of new
grain to the /SCE/XXTERNAL/XX./PR

Leviticus 23:15-17/XX/PR

/PR

/PR

/PR

/PL675/XXSEFIRAT HAòOMER/XX/PR

Thus our ancestors linked Pesah/± and Shavuot as occasions for
thanking God for the fruits of the field. So do we thank God
for the renewal of life which all nature proclaims at this season./PR

/PR

However, as Pesah/± and Shavuot acquired historical significance,
their linkage through the counting of the intervening days took
on new meaning. It connected the idea of freedom, associated
with Pesah/±, with the idea of Torah, associated with Shavuot. It
thus proclaimed that:/PR

